You can accomplish this using the props parameter passed into the custom icon function, however I would need to know your data structure to give more specific guidance. Basically you can check if ```props.record.myArrayofChildren``` exists, and use it as a switch to return your icon or an empty tag. Something like:

```
customExpandIcon(props) {
if (props.record.myChildArray.length &lt; 1) {
  return &lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; //Empty tag, as I think Typescript requires you to return a JSX node
}
if (props.expanded) {
    return &lt;a style={{ color: &#39;black&#39; }} onClick={e =&gt; {
        props.onExpand(props.record, e);
    }}&gt;&lt;Icon type=&quot;minus&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
} else {
    return &lt;a style={{ color: &#39;black&#39; }} onClick={e =&gt; {
        props.onExpand(props.record, e);
    }}&gt;&lt;Icon type=&quot;plus&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
}

}

```

